The code at line 78: `&delta[..newline_pos]` — `find('\n')` returns a byte position. But since `\n` is an ASCII character, it's always at a valid char boundary. In Rust, `find` returns a byte offset, so `delta[..newline_pos]` is safe because we found `\n` at that position via `find`, which guarantees it's on a char boundary.

